name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.namenode.checkpoint.check.period
description:
The SecondaryNameNode and CheckpointNode will poll the NameNode
  every 'dfs.namenode.checkpoint.check.period' seconds to query the number
  of uncheckpointed transactions. Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive),
  as described in dfs.heartbeat.interval.If no time unit is specified then
  seconds is assumed.

name: dfs.block.misreplication.processing.limit
description: Maximum number of blocks to process for initializing replication queues.

name: file.client-write-packet-size
description: Packet size for clients to write

name: dfs.ha.zkfc.nn.http.timeout.ms
description:
The HTTP connection and read timeout value (unit is ms ) when DFS ZKFC
    tries to get local NN thread dump after local NN becomes
    SERVICE_NOT_RESPONDING or SERVICE_UNHEALTHY.
    If it is set to zero, DFS ZKFC won't get local NN thread dump.

name: dfs.datanode.cache.revocation.polling.ms
description:
How often the DataNode should poll to see if the clients have
    stopped using a replica that the DataNode wants to uncache.

name: mapreduce.jobhistory.client.thread-count
description: The number of threads to handle client API requests

name: dfs.namenode.blockreport.queue.size
description: The queue size of BlockReportProcessingThread in BlockManager.
